# Firebase Web SDK config for the maintainer's primary deployment
# (https://email-verifier-ruby.vercel.app/).
#
# These values are PUBLIC by design (they identify the Firebase project, not
# authenticate it). Real security comes from:
#   * Firebase Authorized Domains (Firebase Console -> Authentication ->
#     Settings -> Authorized domains)
#   * Firestore Security Rules (./firestore.rules) - per-uid isolation
#   * Backend ID-token verification on every /api/* request
#
# Forks deploying their own instance should either:
#   1. Override these via Vercel/host env vars (they take precedence at
#      build time), or
#   2. Replace this file with their own Firebase project's values.
#
# NOTE: These values are *deliberately* committed. They are PUBLIC project
# identifiers (not secrets) — Firebase intentionally exposes them in every
# client build (they appear in the Vite bundle's compiled JS, fetchable via
# View Source on the deployed site). Quoting Firebase's own docs:
#
#   "API keys for Firebase services are not used to control access to
#   backend resources; that can only be done with Firebase Security Rules."
#   (https://firebase.google.com/docs/projects/api-keys)
#
# Security comes from Firestore Rules (./firestore.rules), Storage Rules
# (./storage.rules), and the per-uid backend ID-token verification. Wiping
# these values breaks the production build (no Firebase project ID = no
# login), without improving security.
VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIzaSyA1DV4ZGSwaej_ZlF46R3rNWlbdWadgpgc
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=email-verifier-bd.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=email-verifier-bd
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=email-verifier-bd.firebasestorage.app
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=800761823781
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=1:800761823781:web:0a4e03ff3aa300e6eef5cc
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-CYSE64ZN79
